&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note for Welsh students, you must apply via Streamlining where all available jobs can be located&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a motivated individual to join our innovative and pro-active community hospital team to provide skilled, clinical and effective care.&lt;br /&gt;Llynfor ward has 23 beds, minor injuries unit and an out patients with an ongoing ethos of developing multidisciplinary care initiatives addressing the needs of the surrounding population.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate should be able to demonstrate reliability, commitment to providing a high standard of care and the ability to &quot;Think outside the box&quot;.&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an experienced, motivated and enthusiastic registered nurse to join our integrated multidisciplinary team to help provide skilled, clinically effective evidence based nursing care. The post is an exciting opportunity for a trained nurse to develop and build skills within a continually developing learning environment creating a dynamic and modern community hospital for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
